<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-544-444  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 544 444.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lotus  June 1990 v6 n6 p20(1)* Full Text COPYRIGHT Lotus Publishing Corp. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Customer-service clarification. (Lotus Development Corp. will notmerge customer service operations with Novell Inc., WordPerfectCorp.)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   Lotus Development Corp. (press relations).andO;Topic:     Customer RelationsMergerSupport ServicesUser AssistanceSoftware Publishers.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>Customer-Service Clarification About a week after Lotus announced theLotus-Novell merger, the Wall Street Journal reported that Lotus, Novell, andWordPerfect Corp. had combined their customer-service operations.andP;  In aclarification issued the following day, Lotus denied this assertion.andM;It is true that Lotus has established a joint customer-support program withNovell, Banyan Systems, IBM, 3Com Corp., and other network vendors, underwhich Lotus's customer-support staff can call on the network vendors for helpin answering Lotus customers' questions about the operation of Lotus softwareon networks.andM;While the potential exists for expanding this program to include WordPerfect,Lotus has announced no new customer-service or support plans to date.andP;  Lotusdid say that there have been informal discussions among Lotus, Novell, andWordPerfect regarding ways to hand off customer calls.andO;</TEXT></DOC>